      "text": "The server that delivers the client-side javascript that starts you browsing the federated wiki is called the Origin Server. It's special. -- A browser can expect javascript to communicate with the Origin Server. However, browser vendors are skeptical of javascript that tries to communicate with other (remote) servers. There are many security and privacy implications. Federated Wiki employs several mechanisms to appear respectable to modern browsers."
